article.headline: High Point 88, Lees McRae 62
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 26 points to lead High Point to an 88-62 win over Lees-McRae on Tuesday. Reid was among four Panthers scoring in double figures, followed by Troy Bowen with 18 and Mike Jefferson with 17. Jerald Minnis had his first career double-double scoring 13 points and grabbing 13 rebounds. High Point (9-5) built an 18-10 lead with 12:49 left in the first half, but the Bobcats (3-5) went on a 12-2 run to tie the game at 27 at 6:15 in the half. High Point's 9-0 run at the end of the half put the Panthers ahead of Lees-McRae 45-33 at the break. The Panthers pushed early in the second half to gain a 17-point advantage. The Bobcats got within 10 points with 10:26 to play, but could get no closer. Henry Williams scored 15 points to lead Lees-McRae and Aaron Duggar added 10. High Point shot 57 percent from the floor and held Lees-McRae to 36.4 percent shooting.
